text: Sabine Erbs (born 17 July 1964) is a German handball player who played for the West German national team. She was born in Berlin. She represented West Germany at the 1984 Summer Olympics in Los Angeles, where the West German team placed fourth. ==References== Category:1964 births Category:Living people Category:Sportspeople from Berlin Category:German female handball players Category:Olympic handball players of West Germany Category:Handball players at the 1984 Summer Olympics
